{{!--
    Curriculum wayfinding (homepage-start-overhaul 2.6): links a post INTO the
    matching guided /start/ layer so the ~292 articles feed internal PageRank
    into the /start/ hub and its five child pages, and readers discover the free
    five-layer curriculum. Rendered in the POST CONTENT FLOW (post.hbs), NOT the
    desktop-only side rail, so it shows on every viewport (mobile included).

    Keyed on PUBLIC topic tags. {{#has tag=}} cannot see internal hash-* tags —
    the Content API strips them from the post's tag collection (see
    series-nav.hbs / contextual-offer.hbs) — so the hash-pillar-* tags used for
    {{#get}} filters elsewhere would NEVER match here. Tag clusters + branch
    order mirror src/data/pillars.json `priorityOrder` (creator-systems,
    content-systems, tools-and-systems, writing-and-thinking, pkm-foundations,
    knowledge-work, zen-productivity) so the layer we link matches the pillar the
    post is actually assigned to. Two pillars map to one layer
    (creator+content -> Creation, knowledge-work+zen -> Application), so those
    clusters are merged in a single branch. No {{else}} fallback: off-pillar
    posts (e.g. pure dev articles) and non-post contexts render nothing.
--}}
